cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.TYPES, cs.SY. 

This paper deals with type inference and refinement types, which are typically studied in the programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the issue of error messages, which is relevant to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-category. The use of gradual refinement types is related to type systems (cs.TYPES) and the practical implementation of the approach is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
